1. Installed ROS Groovy as shown [here][1] (replacing hydro with groovy).
1. Installed roscopter dependencies:
    ```
    sudo aptitude install ros-groovy-sensor-msgs
    ```
1. Created a ROS / Catkin workspace as shown [here][2].
1. Checked out roscopter & mavlink:
    ```
    cd ~/catkin_ws/src
    git clone https://pechkas@code.google.com/p/roscopter/
    cd roscopter
    git clone https://github.com/mavlink/mavlink.git
    ```
1. At this point, ROS should know about roscopter:
    ```
    rospack list |grep roscopter
    ```
1. Build roscopter (builds mavlink too, I think):
    ```
    rosmake roscopter
    ```
1. Needed to make some changes to get it to run:
    ```
    cd $DIR_CONTAINING_THESE_NOTES
    cp roscopter.patch /tmp
    cd ~/catkin_ws/src/roscopter/mavlink
    touch __init__.py
    cd ~/catkin_ws/src/roscopter
    mv /tmp/roscopter.patch .
    patch -p1 <roscopter.patch
    ```
1. Test with:
    ```
    cd ~/catkin_ws/src/roscopter
    nodes/roscopter.py --device=/dev/null --rate=57600
    ```


[1]: http://wiki.ros.org/hydro/Installation/Ubuntu
[2]: http://wiki.ros.org/ROS/Tutorials/InstallingandConfiguringROSEnvironment#Create_a_ROS_Workspace
